- Call exec() with an object rather than class name.
- No need to include QApplication inside QtWidgets.

After adding QToolButton, it looks like this:
![Screenshot (65)_LI](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16383005/171426264-36f79b9d-aeb4-4de2-b48f-a08a6f3c936c.jpg)

- Currently `mainTabBarCornerWidget->addWidget(toolbarSeparator(false));` not adding a separator and will look into why it is not working.
- Instead of using `QHBoxWidget`, we can shift to `QToolBar`?

pr_body:
- Add `bool maybeSave(int documentId, bool *cancel = nullptr)` which checks if the document has any unsaved changes and returns a bool value if the user pressed `save`, `discard` or `cancel`.
- Add `bool modified;` so that it can modify itself to true and false if there are new changes to the document.
- Add `ConstDatabase` instead of `MemoryDatabase` to make sure the database is not modifiable while getting BRLCAD Object.
- Shift `getBRLCADObject()` inside `Document` class.
